dc_title_s: Map of the Tennessee River for the use of the Mississippi Squadron
dc_description_s: Printed at top of title-page: No. 3019, in 17 sheets. Price.; Detailed map of the Tennessee River from Paducah, Ky., to Florence, Ala., showing soundings, distances from Paducah, fortifications, "Wilson's U.S. Cavalry Camp," vegetation, cultivated fields, houses, names of residents, and roads.; See also Civil War Maps entry no. 519.; Description derived from published bibliography.|each approx. 60 x 46 centimeters|Scale 1:40,000 and 1:500,000|General Map Collection
